t: "As for those who had settled in the city and Ë¹embracedËº the faith before Ë¹the arrival ofËº the emigrants, they love whoever immigrates to them, never having a desire in their hearts for whatever Ë¹of the gainsËº is given to the emigrants. They give Ë¹the emigrantsËº preference over themselves even though they may be in need. And whoever is saved from the selfishness of their own souls, it is they who are Ë¹trulyËº successful"